n_EUd5vmD-L72zPx_Yh2YkMA59nmpV13cNh3l36kowDJC07Xic7_fHUiZZrmVplGtlPLmC0h_Gw2stV7YMKiKOq4aYR9lZ4Eh69wnpGdNcVXzhahzBlW_iB4v_9Bc_I6a9X_GilRScNheV5mosvydJo5ZuzFmeWIhYt44FX25ajeGGuo806xnPL32o7uyiVxeA9_gLgdenoWIik-bFU6ZXzyhjcBQ_UphEDD8MP1TM-dOCgOd48PtRe-1lx_lcdSMGX2L5wxVgKrV8xk_2yAAwa3pffgfElwyXJYxm7UIfyYUjOGmSGWssAlUntIEQy3hmOk0i0drU485iGOD6DXo_akn6wHWevs3n29uJd2sebL39sixj6n00_lSIVFC9btIS-LZwBfTHYZUp833AbOgLY0xCHvYjITbrVknxh-P5qT-C4yoz7do56FYGoevsMoAm3Cj_4NXf_CZNXFCHvlT9gPuFlaQ5r7-lrgTwok8ht4EzH0Q-DpNjtpF88DnC0bvhr_plC-BG1N2KLCIx-e24hJT5KsVHyKolq24Iyb578PoVW3Z5sMoOD0ar6wVFi0lmjdce2JKgpwsoFsScF6iKvQbHDtpgcqjXfPM_Sv-q2LEjw8Cb9ywmNFIvzX49pXVmtCS7GdexZ-MUul2jOYp15ENjJ1PRqaDYN07x4iwxC1ZTjaii9tfl3YJvDsruuQsJvO6qLUIKwWtDlhm9tOWj68R4ZOddNHXG2EklbpsjfOGg2y5iyV5VV29ECgk474pi-e8BNTkGw4_HCe3uOcHP9sD_Ppb1jY294TlR-t5TydeCYoCiPwJR7lJKO9rg4JtXB2cTPwVITxXyjz7AVdKUulxrXqUOp5JJeT6B4Kc50lbCihIjP6u5yFtkdROXLZkRxkkeBtHN47zeBXmO4Xy_gXcuethszHngAQAf8B3lReBovs63f4SoKNEInZXJZoAA4GmeSV0DiueNjtY-AHvYd9IV4Nx70maxTtV1H_H-YguY48-W_sgR1QIJAHqR7iitoI3eplJETKm62h-TD_pjC3kTtQhdHRAsoXX2L8Qy3nwWm7L43POtUi91ZWMnilchPBaIPWI1FRlPTmQJGRuCR1imaMDSl2CivDWAhBU4byo-DYGZKGMdamZE6fGK1QSEFbUO8VE20jdIsz-NMH9QcigPyXzxruVj3Bj3LsLd9yfKvlG-ldjV5q3ewtrGX6usup5wqlgCh73KeFFJGQw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Consolidating test plans**\\n\\nI want to create tests for various functions, like checking if currentDirectory normalizes relative paths and ensuring that DeleteStats records are accurate. For deleteRecursivelyEvenIfInsecure, I need to check if it removes the directory tree while keeping the target of any symlinks intact. I also want to explore how cleanRecursivelyEvenIfInsecure operates. It’s essential to keep track of quiet deletion stats on Linux, especially with secure directories. I'll consider how paths are handled within those tests.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining deletion methods**\\n\\nI need to clarify if Files2.deleteRecursivelyEvenIfInsecure uses CWD_SDS for absolute paths. It seems like the method accepts Path objects, potentially allowing absolute paths, and I want to ensure I’m cautious about that. I should probably stick to relative paths in test runs. I’ll create temporary directories under the current directory for testing, while considering how silent deletion stats should reflect directories and files found and removed. I also want to verify how nonexistent paths and permissions affect file deletion stats.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring secure directory handling**\\n\\nI’m considering the secure variant where reading the NoSuchFile attribute returns zeros, which seems positive. I’m also thinking about using newSecureDirectoryStream for the current directory temp. If it doesn’t have secure directories, I need to assert that it’s unsupported, but I shouldn’t short-circuit the process. It feels crucial to ensure that everything operates smoothly, even if there’s a lack of secure directories. I need to approach this carefully to avoid any potential mishaps!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering temp directory cleanup**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the Files2.deleteRecursivelyEvenIfInsecure function in @TempDir, particularly how it deletes the root. If @TempDir isn't cleaned up, that might be a problem. I'll need to make sure any created directories are cleaned up since TempDir handles this. Also, if creating a symlink fails due to permissions, I need to consider how to handle that without failing. It might be better to catch IOExceptions quietly. I’ll need to test precisely when a symlink is created and how that affects stats.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_aMQHaavcddvSQ9tP8xGkpoyk|fc_0bf73612ac7d5bfc0169f39607f4d48195b697416bc8cdfdfa", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.smallrye.common/smallrye-common-io/2.16.0/src/test/java/io_smallrye_common/smallrye_common_io/SmallryeCommonIoTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_smallrye_common.smallrye_common_io;\n\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.OutputStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.nio.file.DirectoryStream;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.nio.file.SecureDirectoryStream;\nimport java.util.Optional;\nimport java.util.jar.Attributes;\nimport java.util.jar.JarEntry;\nimport java.util.jar.JarFile;\nimport java.util.jar.JarOutputStream;\nimport java.util.jar.Manifest;\n\nimport io.smallrye.common.io.DeleteStats;\nimport io.smallrye.common.io.Files2;\nimport io.smallrye.common.io.jar.JarEntries;\nimport io.smallrye.common.io.jar.JarFiles;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\n\npublic class SmallryeCommonIoTest {\n    @TempDir\n    Path temporaryDirectory;\n\n    @Test\n    void currentDirectoryAndParentResolutionNormalizeRelativePaths() {\n        Path currentDirectory = Files2.currentDirectory();\n\n        assertThat(currentDirectory).isAbsolute();\n        assertThat(currentDirectory).isNormalized();\n        assertThat(Files2.getParent(Path.of(\"alpha\", \"..\", \"beta\", \"child.txt\")))\n                .isEqualTo(currentDirectory.resolve(\"beta\"));\n        assertThat(Files2.getParent(currentDirectory.resolve(\"nested\").resolve(\"..\").resolve(\"leaf.txt\")))\n                .isEqualTo(currentDirectory);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void deleteStatsBehavesLikeARecordValueObject() {\n        DeleteStats stats = new DeleteStats(2, 1, 4, 3);\n        DeleteStats sameStats = new DeleteStats(2, 1, 4, 3);\n        DeleteStats differentStats = new DeleteStats(2, 2, 4, 4);\n\n        assertThat(stats.directoriesFound()).isEqualTo(2);\n        assertThat(stats.directoriesRemoved()).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(stats.filesFound()).isEqualTo(4);\n        assertThat(stats.filesRemoved()).isEqualTo(3);\n        assertThat(stats).isEqualTo(sameStats).hasSameHashCodeAs(sameStats);\n        assertThat(stats).isNotEqualTo(differentStats);\n        assertThat(stats.toString()).contains(\"directoriesFound=2\", \"directoriesRemoved=1\", \"filesFound=4\", \"filesRemoved=3\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void quietRecursiveDeleteReportsRemovedDirectoryTree() throws IOException {\n        Path root = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"quiet-delete-root\");\n        Path nested = root.resolve(\"one\").resolve(\"two\");\n        Files.createDirectories(nested);\n        Files.writeString(root.resolve(\"root.txt\"), \"root\", StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        Files.writeString(root.resolve(\"one\").resolve(\"middle.txt\"), \"middle\", StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        Files.writeString(nested.resolve(\"leaf.txt\"), \"leaf\", StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n\n        DeleteStats stats = Files2.deleteRecursivelyQuietlyEvenIfInsecure(root);\n\n        assertThat(stats).isEqualTo(new DeleteStats(3, 3, 3, 3));\n        assertThat(root).doesNotExist();\n        assertThat(Files2.deleteRecursivelyQuietlyEvenIfInsecure(root)).isEqualTo(new DeleteStats(0, 0, 0, 0));\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void recursiveDeleteRemovesLinksWithoutFollowingThem() throws IOException {\n        Path root = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"delete-root\");\n        Path nested = root.resolve(\"nested\");\n        Path outsideTarget = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"outside-target\");\n        Files.createDirectories(nested);\n        Files.createDirectories(outsideTarget);\n        Files.writeString(nested.resolve(\"payload.txt\"), \"payload\", StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        Files.writeString(outsideTarget.resolve(\"survivor.txt\"), \"survivor\", StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        Optional<Path> symbolicLink = createSymbolicLinkIfSupported(root.resolve(\"target-link\"), outsideTarget);\n\n        Files2.deleteRecursivelyEvenIfInsecure(root);\n\n        assertThat(root).doesNotExist();\n        assertThat(outsideTarget.resolve(\"survivor.txt\")).exists().hasContent(\"survivor\");\n        symbolicLink.ifPresent(link -> assertThat(link).doesNotExist());\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void cleanRecursivelyKeepsDirectoryButRemovesChildren() throws IOException {\n        Path root = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"clean-root\");\n        Files.createDirectories(root.resolve(\"left\"));\n        Files.createDirectories(root.resolve(\"right\").resolve(\"deep\"));\n        Files.writeString(root.resolve(\"left\").resolve(\"left.txt\"), \"left\", StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        Files.writeString(root.resolve(\"right\").resolve(\"deep\").resolve(\"right.txt\"), \"right\", StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        Files.writeString(root.resolve(\"top.txt\"), \"top\", StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n\n        try (DirectoryStream<Path> stream = Files.newDirectoryStream(root)) {\n            Files2.cleanRecursivelyEvenIfInsecure(stream);\n        }\n\n        assertThat(root).isDirectory();\n        try (DirectoryStream<Path> remaining = Files.newDirectoryStream(root)) {\n            assertThat(remaining).isEmpty();\n        }\n\n        Path singleFile = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"single-file.txt\");\n        Files.writeString(singleFile, \"delete me\", StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        Files2.cleanRecursivelyEvenIfInsecure(singleFile);\n        assertThat(singleFile).doesNotExist();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void secureDirectoryOperationsEitherOpenStreamsOrReportUnsupportedFileSystems() throws IOException {\n        Path root = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"secure-root\");\n        Path child = root.resolve(\"child\");\n        Files.createDirectories(child.resolve(\"nested\"));\n        Files.writeString(child.resolve(\"nested\").resolve(\"payload.txt\"), \"payload\", StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n\n        if (Files2.hasSecureDirector